{%- comment -%}
Cloak of Darkness — app-wide layout. Five named blocks (status, heading,
body, choices, footer); rooms override the ones that vary. Un-overridden
blocks fall through to the defaults below. The status block's default
{% include %}s a partial so the cloak readout flows through one file —
the place a translator edits for a new locale. Shared across the five
demo apps so cross-app story composition can target consistent block
names. Phase H wires this; see proposal §3.3 / §5.6.

Whitespace-trim ({%- … -%}) keeps the block-tag scaffolding from
contributing blank lines; the explicit "\n\n" literals between blocks
are the inter-block separators.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- block status -%}{%- include "partials/cloak_status.pongo" -%}{%- endblock %}

{% block heading %}{%- endblock %}

{% block body %}{%- endblock %}

{% block choices %}{%- endblock %}

{% block footer %}{%- endblock -%}
